7a:["$","h2","127",{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4","children":"Conclusion"}]
7b:["$","p","128",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"Gravity feeders excel at reliability, simplicity, and longevity—ideal for pets on consistent routines and owners who prioritize mechanical simplicity. Timed feeders provide precise portion control, schedule flexibility, and remote management—ideal for weight management and multi-pet households."}]
7c:["$","p","129",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"For most households, the best approach combines both:\n- Use a timed feeder (motorized or smart) as your primary feeder for portion control and flexibility\n- Keep a simple gravity feeder as backup for power outages, WiFi failures, and travel\n- This hybrid approach costs ~$250-300 and provides both convenience and reliability"}]
7d:["$","p","130",{"className":"text-gray-700 leading-relaxed my-4","children":"If you must choose one: gravity feeders win for reliability and longevity, while timed feeders win for portion control and flexibility. Your pet's specific needs (weight management vs. routine stability) should determine which takes priority."}]
